Privacy Policy for Super League Greece Alexa Skill
Effective Date: [29/8/2024]

Last Updated: [29/8/2024]

1. Introduction
Welcome to the "Super League Greece" Alexa skill (the "Skill"). Your privacy is important to us, and this Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the Skill.

2. Information We Collect
The Skill may collect certain data to provide a better experience, including:

Voice Interaction Data: We receive and process your voice commands to provide responses.
Device Information: Information such as device type, operating system, and Alexa version may be collected to improve functionality.
User Preferences: Data related to your preferences or settings may be stored to personalize your experience.
3. How We Use Your Information
The information collected is used to:

Provide and improve the Skill's functionality.
Respond to your requests and queries.
Analyze usage patterns to enhance user experience.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not share your personal information with third parties except in the following cases:

Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests.
Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating the Skill, provided they agree to adhere to our privacy standards.
5. Data Security
We are committed to protecting your data and implement reasonable measures to safeguard your information. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

6. Your Choices
You can manage your information and settings through your Alexa app or device settings. You may also disable the Skill at any time.

7. Children's Privacy
The Skill is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Effective Date."

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

